Claims Claims 1. An energy recovery system (114) for a machine (10) having a work tool (16) movable through segments of an excavation cycle, a swing motor (49) configured to swing the work tool (16) about a vertical axis (46), a pump (58) selectively fluidly connected to the swing motor (49) to provide pressurized fluid to cause the swing motor (49) to swing the work tool (16), a power source (88) operatively connected to the pump (58) to output power to drive the pump (58), and a controller (1 10), the energy recover system (114) comprising: a fi r si accumul ator (1 8); a swing charge valve (128) having a normally closed position, an open position, and a charge set pressure, the swing charge valve (128) being positioned to selectively fluidly connect the swing motor (49) to the first accumulator (1 18), wherein the swing charge valve (128) moves from the normally closed position to the open position and fluidly connects the swing motor (49) to the first accumulator (1 18) when a swing motor fluid pressure communicated to the swing charge valve (128) from the swing motor (49) is greater than the charge set pressure; an assist motor (132) operatively connected to the power source (88); and a discharge valve (130) having a normally closed position and an open position, the discharge valve (130) being positioned to selectively fluidly connect the first accumulator (118) to the assist motor (132), wherein the controller (110) is configured to determine a power demand on the power source (88) to output power, and to cause the discharge valve (130) to move from the normally closed position to the open position to fluidly connect the first accumulator (1 18) with the assist motor (132) in response determining that the power demand on the power source (88) is greater than a minimum assisted power demand. 2. The energy recovery system (1 14) of claim 1, wherein the first accumulator ( 18) has a first accumulator maximum charge pressure, and the charge set pressure of the swing charge valve (128) is less than the first accumulator maximum charge pressure. 3. The energy recovery system (114) of claim 1, wherein movement of the discharge valve (130) between the normally closed position and the open position caused by the controller (1 10) occurs independent of a position of the swing charge valve (128). 4. The energy recovery system (1 14) of claim 1, wherein the controller (1 0) is configured to detemiine a first accumulator charge pressure of the first accumulator (118), and the controller (1 10) is configured to cause the discharge valve (130) to move from the normally closed position to the open position to fluidly connect the first accumulator (118) with the assist motor ( 132) in response determining that the power demand on the power source (88) for output power is greater than the minimum assisted power demand and the first accumulator charge pressure is greater than or equal to a minimum accumulator discharge pressure. 5. The energy recovery system (1 14) of claim 2, wherein the machine ( 10) includes a boom hybrid circuit (54) for raising and lowering the work tool (16), wherein the boom hybrid circuit (54) is selectively fluidly connected to the assist motor ( 132) to provide pressurized fluid thereto. 6. The energy recovery system (114) of claim 1 , wherein the machine (10) includes a low-pressure fluid reservoir (60) and a relief valve (76) having a normally closed position, an open position, and a relief set pressure that is greater than the charge set pressure, the relief valve (76) being positioned to selectively fluidly connect the swing motor (49) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60), wherein the relief valve (76) moves from the normally closed position to the open position and fluidly connects the swing motor (49) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60) when the swing motor fluid pressure communicated to the swing charge valve (128) and the relief valve (76) from the swing motor (49) is greater than the relief set pressure. 7. The energy recovery system (114) of claim 6, wherein the machine (10) comprises a low-pressure return passage (78) fluidly connecting 

 the relief valve (76) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60), the energy recovery system (1 14) comprising: a second accumulator (120) fluidly connected to the low-pressure return passage (78); and a back pressure valve (96) having a normally closed position, an open position, and a maximum back pressure, the back pressure valve (96) being positioned along the low-pressure return passage (78) between the relief valve (76) and the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60) to selectively fluidly connect the relief valve (76) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60), wherein the back pressure valve (96) moves from the normally closed position to the open position and fluidly connects the relief valve (76) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60) when a pressure in the low-pressure return passage (78) is greater than the maximum back pressure. 8. A machine (10), comprising: a work tool (16) movable through a range of motion, a swing motor (49) configured to swing the work tool (16) about a vertical axis (46); a pump (58) selectively fluidly connected to the swing motor (49) to provide pressurized fluid to cause the swing motor (49) to swing the work tool (16); a power source (88) operatively connected to the pump (58) to output power to drive the pump (58); the energy recovery system (114) of claim 1; and a controller (1 10) operatively connected to the discharge valve (130), wherein: the controller (110) is configured to determine a power demand on the power source (88) for output power, and the controller (1 10) is configured to cause the discharge valve (130) to move from the normally closed position to the open position to fluidly connect the first accumulator (118) with the assist motor (132) in response determining that the power demand on the power source (88) for output power is greater than a minimum assisted power demand. 9, A method for recovering swing kinetic energy in a hydraulic system (14) of a machine (10), comprising: providing pressurized fluid to a swing motor (49) with a pump (58) of the machine (10) to cause the swing motor (49) to swing a work tool (16) of the machine (10) about a vertical axis (46); sensing a fluid pressure from the swing motor (49) at a swing charge valve (128); opening the swing charge valve (128) to fluidly connect the swing motor (49) to a first accumulator (118) in response to a sensed fluid pressure from the swing motor (49) being greater than or equal to a charge set pressure of the swing charge valve (128) and causing the swing charge valve (128) to move from a normally closed position toward an open position, selectively fluidly connecting the first accumulator (118) to an assist motor (132) via a discharge valve (130), wherein the assist motor ( 132) is operatively connected to a power source (88) of the machine (10); determining a power demand on the power source (88) for output power; and causing the discharge valve (130) to fluidly connect the first accumulator (118) with the assist motor (132) in response determining that the power demand on the power source (88) for output power is greater than a minimum assisted power demand. 10, The method for recovering swing kinetic energy of claim 9, wherein a first accumulator maximum charge pressure of the first accumulator (1 8) is greater than the charge set pressure of the swing charge valve (128). 11 , The method for recovering swing kinetic energy of claim 9, wherein causing the discharge valve (130) to fluidly connect the first accumulator (1 18) with the assist motor (132) occurs independent of a position of the swing charge valve ( 128), 12, The method for recovering swing kinetic energy of claim 9, comprising; 

 determining a first accumulator charge pressure of the first accumulator (1 18); causing the discharge valve (130) to fluidly connect the first accumulator (118) with the assist motor (132) in response determining that the power demand on the power source (88) for output power is greater than the minimum assisted power demand and the first accumulator charge pressure is greater than or equal to a minimum accumulator discharge pressure. 13. The method for recovering swing kinetic energy of claim 9, selectively fluidly connecting a boom hybrid circuit (54) for raising and lowering the work tool (16) to the assist motor (132) to provide pressurized fluid thereto. 14. The method for recovering swing kinetic energy of claim 9, comprising: providing a relief valve (76) between the swing motor (49) and a low-pressure fluid reservoir (60) to selectively fluidly connect the swing motor (49) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir; opening the relief valve (76) to fluidly connect the swing motor (49) to the low-pressure fluid reservoir (60) in response to a swing motor fluid pressure communicated to the swing charge valve (128) and the relief valve (76) from the swing motor (49) being greater than a relief set pressure of the relief valve (76).
